  "notes": "Western Andalusian (Sevilla, Cádiz, Huelva, Córdoba, Málaga). Most phonologically innovative Castilian variety. Hallmarks: coda /s/ → [h] or ∅ (aspiration/deletion), /x/ → [h], universal yeísmo, seseo or ceceo (varies by locality), CH deaffrication [tʃ] → [ʃ] in Cádiz/Sevilla area, coda liquid neutralisation (/l/ ↔ /ɾ/), extreme lenition with consonant deletion, final -n velarisation. Basis for much of Latin American Spanish phonology.",
  "quality": "research",
